===Etymology===
Portuguese [[manga]], from Malayalam [[manga]], Tamil ''mān-kāy''.

Word Mango from Malayalam (language of Kerala, India) Manga. Portuguese explorers tasted mangoes for the first time in Kerala, hence Manga in Portuguese too.

===Noun===
'''mango''' (''plural:'' [[mangoes]])

# A [[tropical]] [[Asian]] [[fruit tree]], ''Mangifera indica''.
# The [[fruit]] of the mango tree.
# ''(US regional)'' A [[bell pepper]].

